    "abstract": "<jats:p> We estimate the sensitivity of scrap decisions to changes in used car values and show how this \u201cscrap elasticity\u201d produces emissions leakage under fuel efficiency standards, a process known as the Gruenspecht effect. We first estimate the effect of gasoline prices on used vehicle values and scrappage of vehicles with different fuel economies. We then estimate the scrap elasticity itself, which we find to be \u22120.7. When applied in a model of fuel economy standards, 13\u201316 percent of the expected fuel savings leak away through the used vehicle market. This effect rivals or exceeds the importance of the often-cited mileage rebound effect. (JEL H23, L62, L78, Q35, Q38, Q48, Q58) </jats:p>",
